 "*": "Quenya"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ring of Barahir"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ruling Queen of Númenor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ruling Queens of Númenor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Rómenna"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sauron"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sceptre"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sceptre of Annúminas"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sceptre of Númenor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Second Age"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Second Age 883"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Silmariën"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Siril"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sorontil"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Taniquelassë"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tar-Aldarion"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tar-Meneldur"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tar-Míriel"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tar-Palantir"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tarmasundar"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Temple"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Line of Elros: Kings of Númenor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lord of the Rings"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Nature of Middle-earth"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Silmarillion"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Three Prayers"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tompollë"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Unfinished Tales"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Vardarianna"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "White House of Erendis"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Witnesses of Manwë"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Yavannamírë"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Yule"}], "templates": [{"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Short description"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:SA"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:References"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:UT"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:App"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:HM"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Numenor"}], "images": [], "wikitext": {"*": "{{short description|Númenórean prayer to Eru in spring}}\nThe '''''Erukyermë''''' was one of the [[Three Prayers]] held on the summit of the [[Meneltarma]] in [[Númenor]] (the others being the ''[[Erulaitalë]]'' and the ''[[Eruhantalë]]''). The ''Erukyermë'' was held at the beginning of each spring. The ruling [[King of Númenor|King]] or [[Ruling Queen of Númenor|Queen]], followed by a silent crowd, would climb the mountain on foot, and at its peak utter a prayer for the approaching year. Traditionally, three [[Eagles]], known by the [[Númenóreans]] as the [[Witnesses of Manwë]], would hover over the King and his people at this time.<ref>{{UT|Numenor}}</ref>\n\nIt was just after the ''Erukyermë'' of {{SA|883}} that [[Tar-Meneldur]], the sixth King of Númenor, surrendered the [[Sceptre]] to his son [[Tar-Aldarion|Aldarion]].<ref name=Ald>{{UT|Aldarion}} (note 16)</ref>\n\nSince Erukyermë marked the beginning of a new year, this points to the existence of a separate calendar for religious purposes, beginning at vernal equinox. For civil matters the [[Edain]] started the year in the middle of winter, just after ''[[Yule]]'', a tradition attested as far back as the [[First Age]].<ref>{{App|D2}}</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\n''Erukyermë'' means \"Prayer to Eru\" in [[Quenya]] (cf. ''[[kyermë]]'').<ref name=Ald/>\n\nA misreading of ''hy'' has been suggested, but the text is a typescript.<ref>\"A typescript made to this point was completed in January 1965.\" from {{HM|UT}}, Introduction</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[Erulaitalë]]''\n* ''[[Eruhantalë]]''\n\n{{references}}\n{{numenor}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Erukyerme}}\n[[Category:Festivals and feasts]]\n[[Category:Númenórean Calendar]]\n[[Category:Quenya names]]"}}}